          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a topological space.
    Then a <fr:em>cohomological Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex></fr:em> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> consists of:

    
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(𝛼) &quot;">
        a complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K_A\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+(X,A)]]></fr:tex>,
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(𝛽) &quot;">
        a filtered complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},F)\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+F(X,\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>,
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(𝛾) &quot;">
        an isomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \colon  K_\mathbb {C}\simeq  K_A\otimes \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+(X,\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p>
            <fr:p>The following axiom has to be satisfied:

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1244</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.2-chc</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.2-chc.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Axiom</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>CHC</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The triple <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}\Gamma (K_A),\mathrm {R}\Gamma ((K_\mathbb {C},F)),\mathrm {R}\Gamma (\alpha ))]]></fr:tex> is a Hodge complex of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
            <fr:p>When <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>, we simply speak of Hodge complexes and cohomological Hodge complexes.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
